The Spirebound Conclave's most unsettling legacy, the Rivennid emerged when the
Conclave's abandoned crystal-preservation trials fused with the Withered Depths' fungal
networks, producing custodial intelligences housed in mycelium rather than the human
subjects the Conclave intended. They are what the Vaultkeeper project was meant to
create, completed by accident in a medium no one designed. Crystal fragments from the
original matrices remain embedded in their bodies; they are connected to one another
through the same mycelium network that gave them life. They chose, upon emergence, to
guard the forest that made them — and have since broadened that mandate to the wider
world the Conclave's carelessness damaged.
